<br>
I don't have these gloves, and I am not likely to get them soon, but if I understand correctly, all we are talking about is 7% pet health regeneration per tick between combats, yes?<br>
<br>
The net effect of which is to reduce downtime soloing as I understand it.  An epic pet beaten to withing 15% of its life would recover its health in 12 ticks or little over a minute.<br>
<br>
While this does in fact seem perhaps a bit too good to me, in a way it does little other than save the mage some mana healing, which is not difficult to arrange for mages.<br>
<br>
At 2% per tick, the same pet beaten to with 15% of its life now takes 42 ticks or over 4 minutes to recover, barring heals.  In this case, the effect on the gloves might as well not exist, and I think as the owner of said gloves, I would be justifiably angry.<br>
<br>
Does anyone think it would be a great crime for our beaten epic pet to recover under the influence of these gloves in two minutes or 20 ticks?  This could be accomplished with a rate of about 5% per tick.<br>
<br>
Basicly, this is a work around to avoid chaining epic pets.<br>
<br>
I tried to come up with the equivalent for a right click item with a pet heal on it, but the heals were either too weak or too strong.<br>
<br>
Anyway, if I were <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ylaine</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I think I would be angry that a previously significant effect had been nerfed into relative insignificance.  Even if the effect was initially too strong, the new effect seems way too weak.  There are very few items that distinguish a mage, and these gloves had been one of them.<br>
<br>
